-- Erste, Komercni Lead Czech Shares Lower After Cheuvreux Report
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-01-09T15:21:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/erste-leads-czech-shares-down-as-cheuvreux-cuts-european-banks.html
Czech stocks dropped for a fourth
day, led by  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)  and  Komercni Banka (KOMB)  AS, after CA
Cheuvreux downgraded European banks to “underweight” from
“neutral.”  The  PX (PX)  gauge declined 1.1 percent to 884.9 by 3:53 p.m. in
 Prague , after a 4.3 percent drop in the previous three sessions.
Austria’s Erste, with a 17 percent weighting in the index, slid
6 percent to 314 koruna, extending last week’s 3.3 percent loss.  Komercni Banka, the Czech unit of Societe Generale SA,
dropped 2.7 percent to 3,155 koruna.  CEZ AS (CEZ) , the country’s
biggest power producer, gained 2.5 percent to 788.5 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
